    "author_association": "NONE",
    "body": "### Problem\n\n`vim.lsp.buf.format` ignores `vim.opt.textwidth` value. Also, I could not specify line width with [formatting options](https://microsoft.github.io/language-server-protocol/specifications/lsp/3.17/specification/#formattingOptions). Please add that ability\n\n### Expected behavior\n\ninserting new line after on formatting `vim.opt.textwidth`",
    "closed_at": "2023-12-31T12:49:11Z",
    "comment_data": [
        {
            "author_association": "MEMBER",
            "body": "> Also, I could not specify line width with [formatting options](https://microsoft.github.io/language-server-protocol/specifications/lsp/3.17/specification/#formattingOptions). Please add that ability.\r\n\r\nThis is up to the specification maintainers, you can raise an issue in https://github.com/microsoft/language-server-protocol/ \r\n\r\nUntil the specification gets extended, and language servers start using it, there's no way we can make use of `vim.opt.textwidth`",
